We have seen greater investment and participation of private sector in many areas of output; we have seen greater and healthier competition in the business sector; we have seen new areas of exportability being developed; and we have seen businesse and ordinary people feeling more confident about themselves. GDP in real terms has gone up by approximately 3 percent yearly in the past two years. Can we ask for more?

But, of course, there are downsides to all these developments. We must be directly concerned with the creation of equal opportunities for our poorer citizens. The income distribution is getting more and more skewed. The rich are getting richer and the poor are getting poorer. However, the Church, according to our pastoral letter, should not only cry out these inequalities; we must cultivate an integral vision to put God back into society to order and re-order ourselves. God had created us to be totally human. Therefore, we must live we Christian virtues such as love, truth, justice, mercy, forgiveness, compassion, self-control.
